# Agent orchestration environment variables

Fields on `Settings` in `app/core/config.py` whose env names start with **`NEXA_AGENT_`** or **`NEXA_AUTO_APPROVE_`** (sub-agent registry, rate limits, autoqueue allowlists, idle cleanup, auto-approve) **must** be reflected in **both** `.env.example` and the repo-root **`.env`** in the same task—see `.cursor/rules/env-vars-sync-dotenv.mdc`.

When adding or renaming these flags, grep both files for `NEXA_AGENT_` and `NEXA_AUTO_APPROVE_` after editing.
